<!-- ── WHAT I DO ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="section" id="what">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="sh-kicker">01 — what I actually do</div>
    <h2 class="sh-title">In plain English.</h2>
    <div class="sh-note">(tap to expand)</div>
  </div>

  <div class="accordion" id="accordion">

    <div class="acc-row" data-open="false">
      <div class="acc-trigger">
        <div class="acc-icon" style="background:#c25a3a">🚜</div>
        <div class="acc-labels">
          <div class="acc-headline">I teach a tiny truck how to drive itself</div>
          <div class="acc-aka">a.k.a. MPPI + PID hierarchical control</div>
        </div>
        <div class="acc-plus">+</div>
      </div>
      <div class="acc-body">
        We took a real electric tow truck — the kind that hauls heavy things around a factory floor — and made it steer itself. No GPS, no fancy roads. It uses a computer brain that imagines a thousand possible futures every fraction of a second, picks the best one, and then smoothly steers toward it.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="acc-row" data-open="false">
      <div class="acc-trigger">
        <div class="acc-icon" style="background:#7a9b6e">🐕</div>
        <div class="acc-labels">
          <div class="acc-headline">I help robot dogs not fall over in the woods</div>
          <div class="acc-aka">a.k.a. FQA-MPPI for quadrupeds</div>
        </div>
        <div class="acc-plus">+</div>
      </div>
      <div class="acc-body">
        A four-legged robot hiking through uneven forest terrain is surprisingly hard. Roots, slopes, loose ground — the robot has to pick where to put each foot before it steps there. My work helps it do that planning fast enough to not trip.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="acc-row" data-open="false">
      <div class="acc-trigger">
        <div class="acc-icon" style="background:#6a7fa3">🔍</div>
        <div class="acc-labels">
          <div class="acc-headline">I build cameras that catch tiny scratches</div>
          <div class="acc-aka">a.k.a. PatchCore visual inspection</div>
        </div>
        <div class="acc-plus">+</div>
      </div>
      <div class="acc-body">
        Manufacturing lines churn out thousands of plastic parts every day. A human inspector gets tired, misses things. I built a camera system that learned what "normal" looks like — now it flags anything that deviates from that. Zero misses in testing.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="acc-row" data-open="false">
      <div class="acc-trigger">
        <div class="acc-icon" style="background:#d4a546">⚙️</div>
        <div class="acc-labels">
          <div class="acc-headline">I write equations that listen to broken machines</div>
          <div class="acc-aka">a.k.a. KAN autoencoders + symbolic regression</div>
        </div>
        <div class="acc-plus">+</div>
      </div>
      <div class="acc-body">
        Imagine holding a stethoscope to a gearbox and having the vibration hum automatically translate into "this gear is cracked." That's the gist. The interesting part: the diagnosis comes out as a readable math formula, not a black box.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="acc-row" data-open="false">
      <div class="acc-trigger">
        <div class="acc-icon" style="background:#8a6f9b">🔌</div>
        <div class="acc-labels">
          <div class="acc-headline">I solder circuit boards for fun (and for power)</div>
          <div class="acc-aka">a.k.a. Custom PCBs + DC-DC converters</div>
        </div>
        <div class="acc-plus">+</div>
      </div>
      <div class="acc-body">
        Every robot or autonomous system needs a power supply that won't fail. I design and build the circuit boards that do this — taking raw battery voltage and converting it cleanly to whatever the motors, sensors, and computers need.
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

